    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="29"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense(M)Colombia/481: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 25, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>159. With reference to paragraph 2 of my telegram “No. 151<note n="53"
                        xml:id="d29fn53">Dated January 23, noon, <ref target="#pg_21">p.
                        21</ref>.</note> and <pb facs="0040" n="26" xml:id="pg_26"/> my telephone
                    conversation with Cissel<note n="54" xml:id="d29fn54">T. Ross Cissel, Assistant
                        Chief, Division of Defense Materials of the Department of State.</note>
                    today, we suggest that a redraft of paragraph 2–<hi rend="italic">a</hi>, which
                    was suggested as an alternative by Urdaneta, be considered: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Rubber Reserve will be able to develop its activities, in the same
                            manner as Caja, in all production zones, but it must inform the
                            Commission in advance of the zones in which it intends to carry on its
                            work. The Government will authorize the respective licenses.[”]<note
                                n="55" xml:id="d29fn55">In telegram No. 113, January 27, 1943, to
                                the Ambassador in Colombia, the Department stated that it was
                                satisfied with this alternative. (811.20 Defense(M)Colombia
                                481).</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
